    "body": "@cammellos  hi!\r\n\r\nI've checked those flows, described in feature request. In fact they work, because we sync contacts of same account on different devices as we used to do it before implementation of contact request functionality. \r\n\r\nAt the same time, there are a few questions in scope of mutual contact requests syncing/pairing:\r\n\r\n1) Are we going to implement syncing of contact request setting value? Currently we don't. So if Device 1 has enabled contact requests - it will not be enabled on paired Device 2\r\n\r\n**CR enabled on paired Device 1**\r\n![photo_2022-07-05 13 28 17](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/97245802/177309005-1ea7a79c-cd3b-4468-b751-67ed72ea1ba3.jpeg)\r\n\r\n**CR disabled on paired Device 2**\r\n![photo_2022-07-05 13 38 23](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/97245802/177310017-4c6263eb-273e-4940-97be-3bdc2033b36a.jpeg)\r\n\r\n2) When paired Device 1 accepts contact request from Device 3, contact request on paired Device 2 will still be in unresolved state in Activity Center, although Device 3 will be added to contacts on both paired Devices 1 and 2.\r\n\r\n**AC of paired Device 1**\r\n![photo_2022-07-05 13 36 07](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/97245802/177309619-523c700c-a317-4bee-a11b-945897d52fb2.jpeg)\r\n\r\n**AC of paired Device 2**\r\n![photo_2022-07-05 13 36 10](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/97245802/177309624-bf85ee3f-2ead-47de-bd57-f0ab9c6f2e13.jpeg)\r\n",
